ed_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### ðŸš€ Feature Request\n\nI would like read-only access to the test tags in my fixtures.\r\nCurrently, only annotations are exposed.\n\n### Example\n\n_No response_\n\n### Motivation\n\nI am preparing the migration of a large e2e testing setup to playwright. \r\nThe biggest pain points we are facing at the moment are:\r\n\r\n- running only necessary tests in CI\r\n- linking features and test implementation\r\n\r\nI would like to achieve this via tags that could look like this: \r\n\r\n- `@feature:{feature_id}` -> this test tests feature with the given id\r\n- `@view:{path}` -> this test touches this view\r\n\r\nThese tags need some enforcement to be useful. So I have implemented an automatic fixture ensuring that each tag type is present in each tests title path. \r\nGuaranteeing that all tests are tagged with both tag types.\r\n\r\nThis is not possible when tags are specified via the details object of a test. \r\nIt isn't exposed in the testInfo object\r\n","closed_by":{"login":"dgozman","id":9881434,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk4ODE0MzQ=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/9881434?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman","html_url":"https://github.com/dgozman","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dgozman/received_events","type":"User","user_view_type":"public","site_admin":false},"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/